## 8. Failure modes and salvage path

- The scaffold has no salvage path (no `salvage` mode). Add one when
  your program needs identity-fallback recovery (canonical example:
  pgas-rag's `salvage` mode entered when verify+citations fail).
- Failure surfaces are reported via the bus's `trigger_failed` and
  `round_execution_failed` events. The consumer's `server/index.ts`
  wires `createSessionLockExhaustedConsumer` (FM2 — pgas#253) so a
  stalled session marks itself Failed rather than freezing.

